The paper deals with text summarization using Seq2Seq models and RNNs, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves techniques for semi-supervised learning, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of neural networks and deep learning suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of RNNs, which is a type of deep learning model, indicating cs.DL (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category as well.
